title: Monthly skilled migration briefing
author: AUSWO Editorial Team

sections.heading: Invitation rounds snapshot
sections.text: Home Affairs has issued two invitations rounds this month, focusing on highly skilled professionals in software engineering, cyber security, and health services. Points cut-offs remain at 85 for the subclass 189 stream.

sections.heading: Regional nomination highlights
sections.text: Queensland and South Australia reopened nomination programs with targeted lists for engineering, health, and hospitality roles. Regional areas continue to offer bonus points for applicants willing to commit to long-term settlement.

sections.heading: Student pathway updates
sections.text: Temporary graduate visa settings remain stable. Graduates in STEM fields are encouraged to transition into the 491 regional stream after completing professional year programs to maximise their invitation potential.

quote: The strongest applications are built on consistent evidence. Keep your documents updated and align your preferences with current state priorities.
